Maximum level: 65<br>
Zone Name: Doomfire (PoFire)<br>
Camp Area/Loc: Picnic table / area before Fennin ramp<br>
Mob List(HP): Doomfire Soldiers, Doomfire Guardians, Doomfire Protectors (40-50k)<br>
Availability (1-&gt;10): 5 (depends on your server)<br>
Loot Ranking (1-&gt;10): 6 (vendor selling items and tradeskill stuff)<br>
Diff.Ranking (1-&gt;10): 9 (high-speed quadding of mobs that quad hit for 900sh a pop)<br>
Gear suggestions: Spell Haste, Jboots, TFlux, ManaPreservation, FT10+<br>
Faction Affected: None<br>
<br>
Other Notes/Tips/Warnings: Best AA grind camp for solo wiz, that I've found so far. There are 9 spawns and room enough to kite them without snaring. MR on these is high enough to not to use snare for quads/9-kites. The spawntime on the 9 also allows for grabbing all 9 and then doing &quot;swarm kite&quot; and finish it before they respawn, thus making med time quite short. Their aggro range is very, very small, so you need to TFlux each one of them to get them to follow, then just round up all 9 and run around the picnic table area. When you use whole area (run behind huts) the long sides of the area give just enough room with JBoots to use pillar or Al'Kabor (and even some buffer if using Pillar of Frost). Using anything over 4s casting time is a suicide. Using just pillar of frost, it is easy to kill first 4, then another 4 and with resists and partials the last one should be around 50% at that time, so it is easy to snare and finish. If you have fast enough Al'Kabor, it can be used to do first 5 and then use pillar on rest 4.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Warning:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->This is not an easy camp, one slip, one lag spike, etc. and you'll be getting rez and new VoQ.<br>
<br>
-myztic <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=plusbrian>plusbrian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/16/03 6:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quad Kiting Locations Guide - Rough Draft</span><hr size=1> Minimum Level:37ish<br>
Maximum Level:43 to ?<br>
Zone Name: IceClad Ocean<br>
Camp Area/LOC: By Eastern Wastes Bridge<br>
Mob List (HP): Dire Wolves (~1300), Frost Giant Scout (~2300), Frost Giant Elites (~2800)<br>
Availability (1-&gt;10): 10 (I've been there for nearly 24 hours real time and never saw anyone else there)<br>
Loot Ranking (1-&gt;10): 5 (some plat and velious weapons, rare Ring of Frost)<br>
Diff.Ranking (1-&gt;10): 3 (Easy)<br>
Faction Affected: Frost Giants (Kromzek and Kromrif decreased, Coldain and Claws of Veshan increased)<br>
<br>
Other Notes/Tips/Warnings: There are tons of dire wolves and Frost Giant Scouts on the southern half island with the EW brdige. Mobs are spread out enough to to avoid adds, yet close enough to quickly pull in a quad. I tend to favor the Giants over the Wolves, primarily because they have some loots (to pay for SoW potions, no luck for me with the <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :sosad --><img src=http://rombusmindspire.tripod.com/sosad.txt ALT=":sosad"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ) and for the Claws of Veshan (eventual Skyshrine quests) and Coldain (Thurgadin quests)faction. There are enough mobs to support 2 or 3 quadders easily, but I never saw anyone else. At around 37 I was getting 1.6 blues per quad, and still getting around 1 blue per quad at 43, although the scouts were starting to turn light blue on me. <br>
<br>
The following are my general quadding notes from my experiences:<br>
<br>
My spell lineup for Quadding<br>
<br>
1: a nuke (not my highest nuke, for finishing up)<br>
2: CoF<br>
3: BoF<br>
4: Root (I use Immobilize, usually for adds)<br>
5: Steelskin (this is mostly because I don't have SoTF and have to get agro by range)<br>
6: Harvest (between rounding up and killing this is usually repoped for each quad)<br>
7: Yonder (for when everything goes awry)<br>
8: Gate (I usually bind at my quad spot, so I usually have Nexus Gate memed for evacing myself, also need to go there often to sell loot)<br>
<br>
Buffs up:<br>
SoW (usually from a potion)<br>
Steelskin<br>
Minor Familar<br>
Greater Shielding<br>
Okiel's Levity<br>
<br>
General approach: <br>
1. As i'm lacking the SoTF <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :sosad --><img src=http://rombusmindspire.tripod.com/sosad.txt ALT=":sosad"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I tend to just run into agro range, which is often through the legs. Snag up four this way <br>
2. Pull mobs to a non add area.<br>
3. switch to eye in the sky mode with f9 (3rd f9 puts you in eye in the sky mode, where you can zoom and in spin around your characters axis). Run in a large circle, such as tapping the right key every .75 seconds or so, usually one circle will group all of them, else do another circle. Use your mouse in pan around to make sure the mobs don't get close enough to whack you.<br>
4. Run a good distance ahead to cast BoF. With the eye in the sky mode I can correctly guess the proper distance every time now.<br>
5. Once they are snared it's all butter from then on out. CoF, walk ahead till gem repops, repeat.<br>
6. Keep track of time on new mobs pulls, make sure to rehit with BoF before it fades.<br>
7. Don't leave home without KEI. <br>
8. Try to get the same mobs in a quad. Not so much because of different HPs, but as long as there is more than 1 mob of the same type chasing you they won't run, they'll keep coming, which is good, else the group will break up because 1 is standing still or running and the other 3 are coming at you.<br>
9. Always be sure to have somehow to quickly resow yourself in case your sow drops.<br>
10. Always have yonder and gate memed when you forget about step 9.<br>
<br>
-Quilottu<br>
44th level wizard of Rodcet Nife <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=plusbrian>plusbrian</A> at: 4/17/03 2:26:27 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=raxheretic>RAXHERETIC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/17/03 1:08 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quad Kiting Locations Guide - Rough Draft</span><hr size=1> Thank you all for your valuable tips I really appreciate it. Great thread!<br>
