Maximum Level:45 to 51<br>
Zone Name: DreadLands<br>
Camp Area/LOC: Giant Fort &amp; Surrounding area<br>
Mob List (HP): Mountain Giants (~1800) <br>
Availability (1-&gt;10): 10 (Only person ever attempted that spawn)<br>
Loot Ranking (1-&gt;10): 7 (some plat and gems, rare Giant Tunic, Leg Smasher, orest Loop)<br>
Diff.Ranking (1-&gt;10): 4 (Easy)<br>
Faction Affected: None <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Notes:   This is an unique quad.   You must be sow or jboots to do this.   The fort it self has 6 mobs  the outside has plenty more.   The major issue is gettting the pull.  Snare, Root, Or TFlux, however. be carefuly.   Now there is a HUGE sheet of ice on the south side of the fort.  Pull them to there.   Also, There are only 2 wanders that go on that huge sheet of ice, plus on the southeast end is a 2 spawn of giants if you run out.<br>
<br>
The main concern is getting them out.  Giants have a longer melee range than most mobs so keep that in mind.  do not pack in front of the fort get them on ice <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
At 41st I had 2 - 2.5 bubbles of mana left after quading.  Maxium amount of mana I used was 3 bubbles of mana.   INT is 251 so you do the math.<br>
<br>
<br>
Have Fun,<br>
<br>
