 </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=plusbrian>plusbrian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/9/03 11:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Quad Kiting Locations Guide - Rough Draft</span><hr size=1> Hiya Nathos,<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>well I decided to try the tofs tower base as mentioned the loot there does suck<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
My main problem there was adds, it was just hard to go anywhere without running into more mobs. I only tried a few times before I move to the southern part of the island and quadding wolves and IG scouts (the southernmost part of the big isle is flat enough (with o'kiels lev) and has few roamers). You get good faction hits (assuing your going on the favorable skyshrine route) and OK loot (2 to 10 plat per mob depending on loot, mostly velious weapons). Anyway, that's what I did at your level.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>but the exp there was merely like one blue to a blue and a half a quad at 36<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Enjoy it while you can, that's about as best your going to get. The most i've ever gotten from a quad is about 8%, and, and most have been more like 5% (1 blue).<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>to make matters worse when these mobs get low the do run rather then chase still like most other mobs when in a pack<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I usually only run into this problem when the mobs are of different types. Usually as long as there is 2 of the same mob, they will always chase you (misery loves company), they being the mobs that are 2 or more. If you have 3 mobs and 2 are of 1 type and 1 of another, the 1 will run and not chase when it gets low on hp.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>this lead to them stopping all together and if I didnt kill them right off they would warp back to where they were pulled from<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
It is a wierd deal, but it will continue happen. My experiences so far are that some mobs will run (when only 1 of there type is left in the quad) and some will gate if you get to far away from them (when they are low on health). What works for me is to not get to far away (not casting at max distance) when the mobs are low on health.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>soooo it is kinda worth it seeing as how with only 240 INT and 230ish mana and kei I could do 3 quads to one of the ultorks before having to med....<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I think part of this is the illusion of it being faster, because you are doing something (gathering the quad, running around) than just sitting there watching your mana bar creep up, e.g. waiting for the proverbial water to boil. To fairly compare these you'll need to time yourself on how much xp you get over a set amount of time. Plus other factors, such as loot and faction. I've determiend a long time ago that I won't quad things for no loot, else I run a defecit in buying SoW potions.<br>
<br>
+quilottu<br>
power gnome of rodcet nife <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gallowaym>gallowaym</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/19/03 10:15 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> 53?</span><hr size=1> after reviewing this guide ive gotten alot of good ideas of where to hunt and what to kill (and even how to do it)  however it seems that the low 50's range is still a little sparse as far as places to hunt.  i was thinking the spirocs in TD. i tried it a couple days ago....lets just say i was looking for a rez within 5 minutes.  is 53 too low for spirocs or did i just do it wrong? and if somebody could also suggest some other hunting spots for 50-55 it would be great!<br>
