-&gt;this is a redo of Myztic's guide, as I arrived to pofire when there were no other elemental guilds: may want to quad with Guardian of Doomfire up. <br>
Minimum level: 65<br>
Maximum level: 65<br>
Zone Name: Doomfire (PoFire)<br>
Camp Area/Loc: Picnic table / area before Fennin ramp<br>
Mob List(HP): Doomfire Soldiers(highly MR), Doomfire Guardians, Doomfire Protectors (40-50k)<br>
Availability (1-&gt;10): 8 - mobs die a bit faster than you can kill them. the camp's always available for me, server varies- there's only one of this area. still the highest xp availability<br>
Loot Ranking (1-&gt;10): 3 - money, but unlike field of gib quads, no rare things to make trades items from. <br>
Quad Diff.Ranking (1-&gt;10): 5  - Uncamped Tactics pit would be a 10(hardest successful quads I have done)... when ranking to make 10 the hardest.<br>
Pull Diff.Ranking(1-&gt;10): 6 - Quavonis Firetail being the hardest mob I've done pulls of for the '10' to compare it against. hard to target.<br>
Gear suggestions:Jboots/SOW, TFlux, ManaPreservation, FT10+, dagger of entrapment helps<br>
Faction Affected: None, or your conscience if you're a Solusek wizard(you killed daddy's defenders?!)<br>
<br>
Location: It's all the way in the back of the zone as you can get yourself; past both fields, the bridge, and the first castle.<br>
<br>
This is a snared version of the three 'sets' of quads. I experience 27% resists at the location to my snare, and a Dagger of Entrapment is very useful for the more limited area. Main danger is the Guardian of Doomfire, who is just ornery and won't let you run around the house that's close to him. I divide this into 3 sets, based on the easiest way to do it:<br>
<br>
First Set, single corner mob.<br>
You'll notice, on entering the area, a mob on the right side of the table area in the back far corner. Since there are 9 mobs, it's optimal to start with him. The easiest way to start is to cast Elnerik's Entombment of Ice on him, then fire snares on him in case of bad luck. You can kite him around the tables or around that area and the back right hut.<br>
<br>
Second Set,first quad.<br>
I have the worst time targeting anything in a hut. You can walk in and proximity guards out if you cant manage to target them(rendering maybe?). Another way is to use eye of tallon to target one. Flux the one on the right side of the left hut(the one by guardian spot) and drag him out. The other two from the other hut can be targeted and fluxed, or you can drag the mob that's chasing you over that hut to add them out. You then should grab the mob from the remaining corner(since trigger's up). Round those up and quad them in the table/back hut area.<br>
<br>
Third set, second quad.<br>
Run to the corner opposite of the two mobs that are standing by the guardian of doomfire. I start this one by getting the remaining one from the hut(just cant target the old boy), then full speed them and pull the other two from the corner around the guardian of doomfire, followed by the last one. Once you start quadding this, the back corner for the third set becomes a territory that's at risk to repopping on you, as the first 3 sets will run you out of mobs, giving you haphazard repop times. <br>
<br>
The other main quadding areas are the soldiers of fire, and the field of gib(which I prefer to the soldiers, for the drops)... which are much easier and I could post on them later! <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showMessageRange?topicID=645.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showMessageRange?topicID=645.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a> <b>3</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=645.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showNextMessage?topicID=645.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=645.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.threadControl?topicID=645.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=645.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=645.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click t